ork%20City%3B%20and%20Samuel%20Altman%2C%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20testifies%20before%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Subcommittee%20on%20Privacy%2C%20Technology%2C%20and%20the%20Law%20May%2016%2C%202023%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ddf7f44ef9f30019f8e2be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times'%20office%20and%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20OpenAI%20CEO.%3Cp%3ELindsey%20Nicholson%2FUCG%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Win%20McNamee%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20has%20been%20holding%20talks%20with%20media%20organizations%20to%20discuss%20a%20licensing%20deal.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20tensions%20with%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20have%20increased%2C%20and%20the%20newspaper%20is%20exploring%20legal%20action%2C%20per%20NPR.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENews%20companies%20are%20concerned%20that%20chatbots%20could%20replace%20them%20if%20trained%20on%20their%20articles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20is%20considering%20suing%20OpenAI%20over%20an%20intellectual%20property%20dispute%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F08%2F16%2F1194202562%2Fnew-york-times-considers-legal-action-against-openai-as-copyright-tensions-swirl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENPR%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20behind%20ChatGPT%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20other%20companies%20with%20AI%20tools%20like%20Google%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20Adobe%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20in%20talks%20for%20months%20with%20media%20organizations%20to%20discuss%20copyright%20issues%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F79eb89ce-cea2-4f27-9d87-e8e312c8601d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20involved%20in%20the%20negotiations%20told%20the%20FT%20that%20news%20publishers%20could%20be%20paid%20a%20subscription%20fee%20by%20AI%20companies%20who%20want%20to%20use%20their%20content%20to%20develop%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT%20and%20Google's%20Bard%20are%20large%20language%20models%2C%20which%20can%20output%20text%20because%20they're%20trained%20on%20vast%20amounts%20of%20data%20scraped%20from%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20media%20companies%20are%20worried%20that%20the%20rise%20of%20chatbots%20could%20turn%20readers%20away%20from%20news%20if%20the%20same%20information%20is%20easily%20accessible%20through%20the%20likes%20of%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NYT's%20top%20concern%20is%20that%20ChatGPT%20is%20becoming%20a%20direct%20competitor%20because%20it%20can%20generate%20text%20that%20answers%20questions%20based%20on%20the%20original%20reporting%20of%20its%20journalists%2C%20according%20to%20NPR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20talks%20between%20The%20Times%20and%20OpenAI%20over%20a%20licensing%20deal%20have%20now%20become%20so%20tense%20that%20the%20newspaper's%20lawyers%20are%20exploring%20whether%20to%20sue%20the%20company%2C%20NPR%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20currently%20unclear%20whether%20OpenAI%20has%20trained%20its%20chatbot%20on%20the%20NYT's%20articles%2C%20but%20if%20a%20judge%20finds%20it%20has%20violated%20copyright%20rules%2C%20it%20could%20be%20ordered%20to%20destroy%20ChatGPT's%20dataset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20executive%20of%20News%20Corp%20%E2%80%94%20which%20owns%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20and%20The%20Times%20of%20London%2C%20and%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20talks%20with%20OpenAI%20%E2%80%94%20said%20in%20a%20May%20media%20conference%20that%20the%20industry's%20%26quot%3Bcollective%20IP%20is%20under%20threat%20and%20for%20which%20we%20should%20argue%20vociferously%20for%20compensation%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20FT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20AI%20was%20%26quot%3Bdesigned%20so%20the%20reader%20will%20never%20visit%20a%20journalism%20website%2C%20thus%20fatally%20undermining%20that%20journalism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-comedian-sarah-silverman-is-suing-the-company-behind-chatgpt-2023-7%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20is%20already%20facing%20a%20copyright%20lawsuit%20from%20authors%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20the%20comedian%20Sarah%20Silverman%2C%20who%20allege%20ChatGPT%20can%20summarize%20their%20work%20even%20though%20they%20didn't%20give%20consent%20for%20their%20books%20to%20be%20fed%20into%20the%20chatbot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20and%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%2C%20sent%20outside%20US%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-times-could-sue-openai-over-tense-licensing-negotiations-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692271470000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ddf809bd8c0900184ede22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-times-could-sue-openai-over-tense-licensing-negotiations-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OpenAI%20has%20been%20holding%20discussions%20with%20several%20news%20organizations%20over%20payment%20for%20developing%20its%20chatbot%20using%20articles%2C%20but%20tensions%20have%20grown.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40insider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-times-could-sue-openai-over-tense-licensing-negotiations-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20than%20a%20ton%20of%20endangered%20pangolin%20scales%20seized%20in%20Thailand%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22