n%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EMinistry%20of%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highways%3A%20Performance%20Audit%20on%20%E2%80%9CImplementation%20of%20Phase-I%20of%20Bharatmala%20Pariyojana%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EFinancial%20Audit%20of%20the%20Accounts%20of%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENHAI%20collected%20over%20Rs%20150%20crore%20from%20commuters%20in%20violation%20of%20toll%20rules%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CAG%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119179%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highways%20Toll%20Operations%20of%20National%20Highways%20Authority%20of%20India%20(NHAI)%20in%20Southern%20India%20has%20found%20that%20in%20five%20toll%20plazas%2C%20a%20total%20amount%20of%20Rs%20132.05%20crore%20was%20collected%20from%20commuters%20in%20violation%20of%20toll%20plaza%20rules.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20audit%20was%20conducted%20on%2041%20randomly%20selected%20toll%20plazas%20across%20the%20five%20southern%20states%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Kerala%20and%20Telangana.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20tabled%20in%20parliament%20on%20August%2010%20stated%20that%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cnon-implementation%20of%20NH%20Fee%20Amendment%20Rules%202013%20dated%2016%20December%202013%20with%20respect%20to%20upgradation%20of%20existing%20four%20lane%20highways%2C%20NHAI%20continued%20to%20collect%20user%20fee%20in%20three%20toll%20plazas%20(namely%20Nathavalasa%2C%20Chalageri%2C%20Hebbalu)%20during%20delayed%20period%20of%20construction%20though%20the%20amended%20rule%20stated%20that%20no%20user%20fee%20shall%20be%20levied%20for%20the%20delayed%20period.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20this%20resulted%20in%20the%20collection%20of%20user%20fees%20of%20Rs%20124.18%20crore%20during%20the%20period%20May%202020%20to%20March%202021%20in%20%E2%80%9Cviolation%20of%20the%20amended%20toll%20fee%20rules%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20at%20the%20Paranur%20toll%20plaza%2C%20the%20NHAI%20delayed%20reduction%20in%20user%20fee%20to%2075%25%20of%20fee%20applicable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F14113428%2FToll_Plaza_on_Roads_in_India_NH_27_National_Highway_Rajasthan_NH76_old_system_in_India.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22688%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F14113428%2FToll_Plaza_on_Roads_in_India_NH_27_National_Highway_Rajasthan_NH76_old_system_in_India.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F14113428%2FToll_Plaza_on_Roads_in_India_NH_27_National_Highway_Rajasthan_NH76_old_system_in_India-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F14113428%2FToll_Plaza_on_Roads_in_India_NH_27_National_Highway_Rajasthan_NH76_old_system_in_India-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-420527%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22459%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20TeshTesh%2FCC%20BY%20SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20Madpam%20toll%20plaza%2C%20the%20NHAI%20annually%20revised%20the%20user%20fee%20despite%20the%20stipulation%20of%20no%20revision%20during%20upgradation%20as%20per%20the%20amended%20Fee%20Rules.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENHAI%20collected%20Rs%207.87%20crore%20from%20road%20users%20on%20the%20two%20toll%20plazas%20from%20August%202018%20to%20March%202021.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThus%20toll%20collection%20in%20these%20five%20toll%20plazas%20led%20to%20undue%20burden%20of%20Rs%20132.05%20crore%20on%20road%20users%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20stated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20that%20NHAI%20collected%20excess%20toll%20fees%20of%20Rs%2022.10%20crore%20from%20road%20users%20during%202017-2018%20to%202020-2021%20at%20the%20Paranur%20public-funded%20toll%20plaza.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20bridge%20had%20been%20constructed%20in%201954%20and%20a%20user%20fee%20was%20being%20collected%20for%20it%2C%20again%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20NH%20Fee%20Second%20Amendment%20Rules%202011.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20rules%2C%20since%20the%20bridge%20was%20constructed%20prior%20to%201956%2C%20the%20user%20fee%20was%20not%20to%20be%20levied.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20audit%20also%20found%20that%20delays%20in%20toll%20collection%20according%20to%20time%20limits%20prescribed%20by%20NH%20Fee%20Rules%2C%202008%2C%20in%20four%20stretches%20of%20public%20funded%20projects%20led%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20NHAI%20revenue%20amounting%20to%20Rs%2064.60%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fformer-shimla-dy-mayor-alleges-criminal-negligence-nhai%5C%22%3EShimla%20Ex-Deputy%20Mayor%20Files%20FIR%20Against%20NHAI%2C%20Alleges%20It%20Violated%20Environmental%20Norms%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENHAI%20also%20lost%20revenue%20of%20Rs%20133.36%20crore%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20provision%20for%20revenue%20sharing%20for%20two%20sections%20of%20NH%2044%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20constructed%20by%20NHAI%20and%20handed%20over%20to%20BOT%20(Build%2C%20Operate%2C%20Transfer%20toll)%20concessionaires%20for%20toll%20collection.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E52%25%20routes%20under%20UDAN%20scheme%20not%20operational%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CAG%20report%20on%20the%20r%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eegional%20connectivity%20scheme%20UDAN%20(%3Cem%3EUde%20Desh%20Ka%20Aam%20Naagrik%3C%2Fem%3E)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eunder%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Civil%20Aviation%20has%20found%20that%20up%20to%20March%202021%2C%20when%20UDAN-3%20ended%2C%2052%25%20(403%20out%20of%20774%20routes)%20of%20the%20awarded%20routes%20could%20not%20commence%20operations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scheme%20launched%20in%202016%20is%20aimed%20at%20promoting%20affordability%20of%20regional%20air%20connectivity%20and%20refurbishing%20underserved%20airports.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20of%20the%20371%20commenced%20routes%2C%20only%2030%25%20(112%20routes)%20completed%20the%20full%20concession%20period%20of%20three%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20out%20of%20these%20112%20routes%2C%20only%2054%20routes%20(7%25%20of%20the%20awarded%20routes)%20connecting%2017%20RCS%20%5Bregional%20connectivity%20scheme%5D%20airports%20could%20sustain%20the%20operations%20beyond%20the%20concession%20period%20of%20three%20years%2C%20as%20of%20March%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20stated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20delays%E2%80%9D%20in%20revival%20or%20development%20of%20identified%20RCS%20airports%20out%20of%20the%20budgetary%20support%20sanctioned%20by%20Cabinet%20Committee%20on%20Economic%20Affairs%20in%20March%202017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COut%20of%20the%20116%20airports%2F%20heliports%2Fwater%20aerodromes%20where%20expenditure%20was%20incurred%2C%20operations%20commenced%20at%20only%2071%20(61%25)%20airports%2Fheliports%2Fwater%20aerodromes%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COperations%20could%20not%20be%20commenced%20or%20were%20discontinued%20at%2083%20airports%2Fheliports%2Fwater%20aerodromes%20even%20after%20incurring%20an%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%201%2C089%20crore.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fudan-scheme-problems-beyond-covid-19-pandemic%5C%22%3EPandemic%20Yes%2C%20but%20Problems%20With%20the%20UDAN%20Scheme%20Also%20Go%20Beyond%20That%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIrregularities%20in%20highway%20projects%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20report%20of%20highway%20projects%20under%20the%20Implementation%20of%20Bharatmala%20Pariyojana%20Phase-I%20(BPP-1)%C2%A0%20has%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-finds-irregularities-in-award-of-highway-projects-under-bharatmala-pariyojana%5C%22%3Einstances%20of%20irregularities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CInstances%20of%20irregularities%20in%20award%20of%20projects%20by%20implementing%20agencies%20were%20observed%20in%20clear%20violation%20of%20the%20prescribed%20processes%20of%20tendering%2C%20viz.%2C%20successful%20bidder%20not%20fulfilling%20tender%20condition%20or%20bidder%20selected%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20falsified%20documents%2C%20award%20of%20works%20without%20there%20being%20approved%20detailed%20project%20reports%20or%20based%20on%20faulty%20detailed%20project%20report%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20huge%20overrun%20costs%20in%20the%20Dwarka%20Expressway%20project%20which%20was%20prioritised%20to%20decongest%20NH-48%20between%20Delhi%20to%20Gurugram%20by%20developing%20it%20into%2014-lane%20national%20highway.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%