Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20financial%20year%20(FY)%202021-22%20the%20ministry%20had%20unsanctioned%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%2023%2C885.47%20crore%2C%20encompassing%201%2C937%20cases.%20In%20FY%202020-21%20unsanctioned%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%208%2C127.97%20crore%20was%20incurred%20by%20Indian%20Railways%20in%202%2C775%20cases.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSimilar%20audit%20comments%20were%20made%20in%20the%20previous%20C%26amp%3BAG%20audit%20reports%20for%20the%20year%202018-19%20to%202020-21.%20Thus%2C%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20no%20steps%20had%20been%20taken%20by%20the%20Ministry%20to%20reduce%20the%20cases%20of%20unsanctioned%20expenditure%20despite%20being%20pointed%20out%20in%20the%20previous%20C%26amp%3BAG%20audit%20reports%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETrend%20analysis%20of%20object%20head%20wise%20expenditure%20in%20respect%20of%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%2C%20Cooperation%20and%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Welfare%20revealed%20persistent%20savings%20of%2040%25%20to%2096%25%20of%20the%20Budget%20Estimate%20during%20the%20last%20five%20years.%20The%20report%20said%20that%20this%20indicates%20deficient%20planning%20at%20the%20Budget%20Estimate%20stage%20without%20taking%20into%20account%20previous%20years%E2%80%99%20trends.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692270086000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F17162535%2FUntitled-design-9.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-nhai-toll-collection-railway-bharatmala-udan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20part%20one%20of%20this%20series%2C%20'The%20Wire'%20sums%20up%20what%20the%20first%20four%20of%2012%20reports%20filed%20by%20the%20CAG%20say%20on%20government%20functioning%20and%20corruption.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-nhai-toll-collection-railway-bharatmala