ider.com%2Fwhat-is-starbucks-cold-foam-vanilla-sweet-cream-iced-coffee-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20%241.25%20add-on%20was%20first%20rolled%20out%20at%20regular%20Starbucks%20stores%20in%202018.%20Starbucks%20currently%20sells%20it%20in%20six%20flavors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gdean%40insider.com%20(Grace%20Dean)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-starbucks-cold-foam-vanilla-sweet-cream-iced-coffee-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20fight%20over%20'return%20to%20office'%20policies%20has%20a%20dirty%20downside%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20small%20globe%20symbolizing%20the%20earth%20sits%20in%20a%20trash%20bin%20full%20of%20thrown%20away%20bunches%20of%20paper.%20The%20trash%20bin%20is%20sandwiched%20in%20between%20two%20large%20gray%20file%20cabinets%20in%20front%20of%20a%20dull%20beige%20wall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da92b05e5d5a00195ddcbd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReturn%20to%20office%20mandates%20also%20come%20with%20a%20return%20to%20dirty%2C%20carbon-emitting%20commutes.%3Cp%3EArantza%20Pena%20Popo%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPush%20to%20end%20work-from-home%20could%20make%20climate%20crisis%20worse%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERachel%20really%20hates%20sitting%20in%20traffic.%20Knowing%20she's%20about%20to%20spend%20up%20to%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20in%20her%20car%20that%20day%20staring%20at%20taillights%20in%20front%20of%20her%20makes%20it%20all%20the%20more%20difficult%20to%20wake%20up%20in%20the%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20a%20remote%20position%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20but%20landed%20a%20new%20job%20in%20February%20at%20a%20nonprofit%2C%20which%20came%20with%20a%20catch%3A%20The%20job%20required%20her%20to%20make%20the%20hike%20to%20its%20Silver%20Spring%2C%20Maryland%2C%20office%20at%20least%20two%20days%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20forcing%20her%20to%20commute%2030%20to%2045%20minutes%20each%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERachel%2C%20who%20was%20granted%20a%20pseudonym%20to%20speak%20freely%20about%20her%20employer's%20policy%2C%20is%20among%20millions%20of%20workers%20getting%20back%20into%20the%20swing%20of%20commuting%20thanks%20to%20return-to-office%20mandates.%20Like%20many%20of%20them%2C%20Rachel%20said%20she%20doesn't%20see%20the%20point.%20But%20it's%20not%20just%20the%20time%20suck%20that%20bothers%20her%2C%20it's%20the%20environmental%20impact%20of%20her%20new%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20get%20kind%20of%20furious%20when%20I%20drive%20to%20work%20and%20see%20the%20road%20choked%20with%20traffic%2C%26quot%3B%20Rachel%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20incredibly%20harmful%20to%20the%20environment.%20And%20offices%20also%20generate%20so%20much%20waste%2C%20like%20paper%20and%20plastic%20cups%20and%20utensils.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERachel's%20concerns%20about%20the%20environment%20have%20been%20largely%20ignored%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-making-workers-employees-return-to-office-rto-wfh-hybrid-2023-1%5C%22%3Ethe%20battle%20over%20return-to-office%20mandates%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20publicly.%20CEOs%20at%20Amazon%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20argue%20that%20in-person%20collaboration%20and%20random%20watercooler%20conversations%20keep%20people%20more%20engaged.%20Opponents%20of%20the%20shift%20have%20emphasized%20the%20ability%20of%20workers%20to%20be%20more%20productive%20when%20they%20set%20their%20own%20schedule.%20But%20grappling%20with%20the%20broader%20planetary%20effects%20of%20these%20decisions%20is%20a%20failure%20on%20the%20part%20of%20corporations%2C%20James%20Elfer%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20More%20Than%20Now%2C%20told%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20shocking%20that%20this%20isn't%20part%20of%20the%20conversation%2C%20especially%20at%20companies%20that%20claim%20to%20care%20about%20sustainability%2C%26quot%3B%20Elfer%2C%20whose%20firm%20conducts%20behavioral-science%20experiments%20to%20improve%20workplaces%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20missed%20opportunity%20to%20explore%20an%20employer's%20colossal%20influence%20on%20our%20behavior.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20mandatory%20return-to-office%20policies%20will%20make%20the%20climate%20crisis%20worse%20is%20an%20important%20question%2C%20especially%20as%20scientists%20predict%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsummer-2023-heat-wave-tracker-temperature-records-2023-5%5C%22%3E2023%20will%20be%20the%20hottest%20year%20on%20record%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Transportation%20accounts%20for%20about%2015%25%20of%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20warming%20the%20planet%2C%20with%20gas-powered%20cars%2C%20trucks%2C%20and%20buses%20contributing%20an%20outsize%20amount.%20But%20determining%20whether%20working%20from%20an%20office%20is%20worse%20for%20the%20planet%20isn't%20that%20simple.%20There%20are%20myriad%20factors%20that%20could%20tip%20the%20scales%20the%20other%20way%2C%20such%20as%20where%20people%20live%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20energy%20people%20use%20at%20home%2C%20the%20food%20they%20eat%2C%20the%20things%20they%20buy%2C%20and%20the%20extra%20trips%20they%20take.%20We%20are%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20major%20upheaval%20in%20how%20people%20work%2C%20and%20Fortune%20500%20companies%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prnewswire.com%2Fnews-releases%2Ffortune-announces-2022-fortune-500-list-301552608.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520revenue%2520threshold%2520for%25202022%2Cemploy%252029.7%2520million%2520people%2520worldwide.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemploy%20nearly%2030%20million%20people%20around%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Failing%20to%20find%20a%20balance%20between%20boosting%20productivity%20at%20the%20office%20and%20protecting%20the%20planet%20risks%20making%20the%20crisis%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCollectively%2C%20these%20decisions%20mean%20millions%20of%20employees%20working%20in%20profoundly%20different%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20Elfer%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20lack%20of%20attention%20feels%20irresponsible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECommuting%20cost%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20the%20transportation%20sector%20belches%20out%20the%20most%20greenhouse%20gases%20of%20any%20industry%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fgreenvehicles%2Ffast-facts-transportation-greenhouse-gas-emissions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassenger%20vehicles%20are%20largely%20responsible%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20generating%20the%20equivalent%20of%20374%20million%20metric%20tons%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20in%202021.%20While%20all%20that%20driving%20isn't%20just%20from%20commuting%2C%20about%20three-fourths%20of%20the%20154%20million%20Americans%20who%20do%20travel%20to%20work%20go%20by%20car.%20On%20average%2C%20they%20spend%20nearly%20an%20hour%20on%20the%20road%20each%20day%2C%20according%20to%20US%20Census%20data%20from%202021.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fstatistics%2Ftransport-statistics-great-britain-2022%2Ftransport-statistics-great-britain-2022-domestic-travel%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrends%20are%20similar%20in%20the%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20cars%20and%20taxis%20account%20for%20half%20of%20the%20transportation%20sector's%20emissions%2C%20and%20some%2068%25%20percent%20of%20people%20who%20commute%20to%20work%20did%20so%20by%20car%20for%20an%20average%20travel%20time%20of%20one%20hour%20a%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20it%20stands%20to%20reason%20that%20cutting%20out%20commutes%20would%20help%20keep%20the%20air%20cleaner.%20Ty%20Colman%2C%20a%20cofounder%20and%20the%20chief%20revenue%20officer%20at%20Optera%2C%20a%20carbon-accounting%20firm%20that%20helps%20organizations%20quantify%20their%20emissions%2C%20said%20that%20in%20general%2C%20a%20fully%20remote%20company%20with%20no%20offices%20has%20the%20lowest%20impact-per-employee%20per%20year%2C%20at%20less%20than%201%20metric%20ton%20of%20carbon-dioxide%20equivalent.%20That%20includes%20the%20uptick%20in%20energy%20used%20to%20power%20computers%2C%20keep%20the%20lights%20on%2C%20and%20maintain%20a%20comfortable%20temperature%20at%20home.%20Employees%20with%20a%20hybrid-work%20policy%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20be%20remote%20three%20days%20a%20week%20emit%20about%201.4%20metric%20tons%20per%20year%2C%20which%20increases%20to%201.7%20metric%20tons%20under%20a%20fully%20in-office%20policy.%20The%20firm's%20method%20is%20based%20on%20the%20Greenhouse%20Gas%20Protocol%2C%20the%20most%20widely%20used%20standard%20among%20organizations%2C%20cities%2C%20and%20countries%20to%20track%20their%20emissions.%20The%20company%20adjusted%20a%20wide%20array%20of%20variables%20to%20see%20how%20different%20behaviors%20affected%20the%20amount%20of%20emissions%20per%20employee%2C%20Colman%20said%2C%20and%20fully%20in-office%20always%20produced%20the%20highest%20emissions%20unless%20a%20large%20majority%20of%20people%20made%20their%20commute%20by%20public%20transit%20%E2%80%94%20then%20a%20hybrid%20schedule%20could%20actually%20have%20a%20greater%20environmental%20impact.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Fcommentaries%2Fworking-from-home-can-save-energy-and-reduce-emissions-but-how-much%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Energy%20Agency%20in%202020%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20for%20people%20who%20commute%20more%20than%204%20miles%20per%20day%20by%20car%2C%20their%20emissions%20would%20decrease%20if%20they%20worked%20from%20home.%20Overall%2C%20if%20people%20who%20can%20telework%20did%20so%20just%20one%20day%20a%20week%2C%20it%20would%20cut%2024%20million%20metric%20tons%20of%20emissions%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20equivalent%20to%20what%20the%20Greater%20London%20area%20produces%20each%20year.%20The%20IEA%20said%20that%20represented%20a%20%26quot%3Bnotable%20decline%26quot%3B%20but%20was%20small%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20amount%20emissions%20must%20drop%20to%20meet%20global%20climate%20goals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3E%26quot%3BI%20get%20kind%20of%20furious%20when%20I%20drive%20to%20work%20and%20see%20the%20road%20choked%20with%20traffic.%20It's%20incredibly%20harmful%20to%20the%20environment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20onset%20of%20the%20pandemic%20in%202020%20provided%20a%20real-world%20opportunity%20to%20research%20what%20happens%20when%20millions%20of%20people%20stop%20commuting%20and%20work%20from%20home.%20Ralf%20Martin%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20Imperial%20College%20Business%20School%20in%20London%2C%20did%20just%20that.%20His%20team%20collected%20smart-meter%20data%20from%20a%20representative%20sample%20of%201%2C164%20UK%20households%20and%20surveyed%20452%20of%20them%20about%20how%20their%20daily%20patterns%20changed%20during%20July%20and%20August%202020.%20Most%20people%20reported%20a%20commute%20of%20fewer%20than%2020%20miles%20and%20traveled%20by%20car.%20On%20average%2C%20they%20worked%20from%20home%20three%20days%20a%20week%20and%20commuted%20two%2C%20as%20some%20were%20essential%20workers%20and%20had%20to%20go%20in.%20Even%20as%20people%20sat%20at%20home%20charging%20laptops%20and%20taking%20video%20calls%2C%20overall%20household%20emissions%20dropped%20by%2033%25%20%E2%80%94%20electricity%20use%20went%20up%20by%206%25%2C%20while%20gas%20consumption%20decreased%20by%209.5%25.%20That%20rise%20in%20electricity%20didn't%20generate%20as%20big%20a%20spike%20in%20emissions%20as%20expected%2C%20Martin%20said%2C%20for%20two%20reasons%3A%20First%2C%20demand%20was%20more%20spread%20out%20during%20the%20day.%20In%20the%20pre-COVID%20world%2C%20household%20emissions%20were%20clustered%20in%20the%20early%20morning%20and%20the%20evenings%2C%20forcing%20more%20inefficient%20oil%20and%20gas%20plants%20to%20come%20online%20to%20meet%20the%20spikes%20in%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20these%20morning%20and%20evening%20peaks%20is%20when%20energy%20generation%20is%20the%20dirtiest%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20high%20demand%20leads%20to%20some%20of%20the%20more%20marginal%2C%20dirtier%20power%20plants%20getting%20switched%20on%20so%20the%20carbon%20intensity%20of%20the%20power%20grid%20goes%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20factor%20was%20a%20bit%20more%20odd%3A%20Since%20people%20weren't%20going%20into%20the%20office%20and%20spending%20time%20around%20colleagues%2C%20they%20probably%20care%20less%20about%20hygiene.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20also%20possible%20people%20didn't%20shower%20so%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20added.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20less%20energy%20for%20heating%20water.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20study%20only%20covered%20the%20early%20part%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20illustrated%20how%20a%20shift%20away%20from%20office%20work%20can%20have%20some%20positive%20effects%20for%20the%20planet.%20But%20since%20we%20are%20no%20longer%20in%20lockdown%2C%20global%20emissions%20have%20rebounded%20to%20higher%20than%20pre-pandemic%20levels%20because%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-airlines-expects-memorial-day-travel-beat-pre-pandemic-levels-2023-5%5C%22%3Eare%20driving%20and%20flying%20again%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20IEA%20said.%20The%20added%20trouble%20is%20that%20many%20people%20used%20the%20pandemic%20as%20a%20reason%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-leaving-cities-for-suburbs-amid-pandemic-2020-11%5C%22%3Emove%20to%20the%20suburbs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20potentially%20means%20longer%20and%20more%20expensive%20commutes%20as%20employers%20demand%20people%20be%20in%20the%20office%20again%20%E2%80%94%20making%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20more%20flexibility%20to%20work%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bottom%20line%20here%20is%20that%20the%20immediate%20effect%20was%20this%20big%20savings%20in%20emissions%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20what%20seems%20to%20be%20emerging%20is%20a%20danger%20that%20transport%20emissions%20are%20actually%20increasing%20as%20people%20move%20further%20away%20from%20their%20place%20of%20work%20and%20engage%20in%20hybrid%20working.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EKeeping%20the%20lights%20on%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20intuitive%20nature%20of%20the%20argument%2C%20most%20experts%20said%20that%20sending%20everyone%20back%20to%20home%20offices%20is%20not%20a%20silver%20bullet%20for%20combating%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20If%20a%20person's%20commute%20was%20shorter%20than%204%20miles%20or%20they%20relied%20on%20public%20transportation%2C%20the%20IEA%20report%20found%2C%20teleworking%20could%20actually%20increase%20their%20emissions%20because%20of%20the%20extra%20energy%20used%20at%20home.%20Other%20behaviors%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20this%20calculation%2C%20as%20well%3A%20What%20time%20of%20year%20is%20it%3F%20During%20the%20winter%2C%20energy%20use%20tends%20to%20be%20higher%20as%20people%20turn%20on%20the%20heat%2C%20though%20in%20the%20US%20it's%20actually%20higher%20in%20the%20summer%20because%20air%20conditioning%20is%20so%20common.%20Are%20people%20wasting%20more%20food%20or%20running%20their%20electronic%20devices%20unnecessarily%3F%20Running%20more%20errands%3F%20Taking%20more%20weekend%20trips%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20More%20Than%20Now%20outlined%20a%20road%20map%20for%20how%20companies%20could%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2022%2F03%2Fis-remote-work-actually-better-for-the-environment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetermine%20the%20optimal%20mix%20of%20commuting%20and%20WFH%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20employees.%20The%20firm's%20initial%20research%20found%20that%20employees'%20net-sustainability%20impact%20depended%20on%20travel%2C%20the%20energy%20and%20digital%20devices%20they%20use%2C%20waste%20management%2C%20and%20local%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEach%20was%20dramatically%20influenced%20by%20remote%20work%20and%20had%20pros%20and%20cons%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20our%20environmental%20footprint%2C%26quot%3B%20Elfer%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20clear%20answer%20to%20whether%20work%20from%20home%20was%20better%20or%20worse%20for%20the%20environment%20in%20general%20terms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EIt's%20shocking%20that%20this%20isn't%20part%20of%20the%20conversation%2C%20especially%20at%20companies%20that%20claim%20to%20care%20about%20sustainability%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ETailoring%20people's%20behavior%20to%20ensure%20that%20working%20from%20home%20actually%20cuts%20emissions%20can%20be%20hard%2C%20especially%20without%20robust%20data%20from%20employees%20on%20how%20they%20spend%20their%20time.%20Even%20without%20this%20information%2C%20some%20institutions%20are%20encouraging%20people%20to%20be%20more%20sustainable%20at%20home%2C%20including%20American%20University%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20Megan%20Litke%2C%20the%20director%20of%20sustainability%20at%20American%2C%20said%20her%20office%20conducts%20a%20survey%20each%20year%20of%20faculty%20and%20staff%20to%20track%20their%20commuting%20habits.%20However%2C%20they%20haven't%20found%20a%20way%20to%20accurately%20measure%20what%20people%20are%20doing%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20taken%20the%20approach%20that%20we%20don't%20need%20a%20firm%20number%20to%20start%20taking%20action%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Litke%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20provide%20people%20with%20a%20list%20of%20actions%20they%20can%20do%2C%20broken%20out%20by%20morning%20routine%2C%20lunch%20break%2C%20and%20afternoon%20stretch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.american.edu%2Fabout%2Fsustainability%2Fget-involved%2Fgreen-home-guide.cfm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreen%20Home%20Guide%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20avoid%20plastic%20K-Cups%20for%20coffee%20and%20eat%20meat-%20and%20dairy-free%20meals%20to%20lower%20their%20carbon%20footprint%2C%20and%20it%20offers%20tips%20for%20recycling%2C%20composting%2C%20and%20buying%20green%20cleaning%20products.%20Energy-saving%20techniques%20are%20also%20included%2C%20such%20as%20putting%20desks%20near%20a%20window%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20daylight%20and%20setting%20electronic%20devices%20to%20go%20into%20sleep%20mode%20after%20a%20certain%20window%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20to%20recognize%20that%20working%20from%20home%20isn't%20a%20perfect%20environmental%20solution%2C%26quot%3B%20Litke%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20think%20about%20it%20holistically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHead%20in%20the%20sand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20scientists%20and%20experts%20are%20trying%20to%20find%20the%20perfect%20mix%20of%20work-from-home%20and%20in-office%20time%20to%20help%20the%20planet%2C%20CEOs%20seem%20less%20concerned.%20Many%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20even%20ones%20that%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-crisis-inequality-racial-justice-energy-technology-innovation-2022-11%5C%22%3Ethey%20are%20dedicated%20to%20helping%20the%20planet%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20seem%20interested%20in%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20answer%2C%20Efler%20said.%20More%20Than%20Now%20published%20its%20road%20map%20in%202021%20in%20hopes%20that%20companies%20would%20want%20to%20partner%20to%20study%20the%20trade-offs%2C%20but%20in%20the%20two%20years%20since%20his%20organization%20started%20looking%20into%20the%20issue%2C%20it's%20been%20mostly%20crickets%20from%20the%20corporate%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOperta's%20Colman%20said%20that%20companies%20are%20quietly%20considering%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20emissions%20will%20be%20relative%20to%20various%20work%20policies.%26quot%3B%20It%20may%20not%20be%20center%20stage%20in%20the%20debate%20because%20employees'%20commutes%20can%20represent%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20a%20company's%20overall%20emissions%2C%20Colman%20said%2C%20but%20Optera%2C%20which%20has%20clients%20including%20Target%2C%20Dell%2C%20and%20Williams-Sonoma%2C%20has%20run%20the%20numbers%20for%20dozens%20of%20companies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20question%20at%20hand%20and%20the%20volume%20of%20the%20environmental%20promises%20made%20by%20many%20large%20corporations%2C%20the%20relative%20hush%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20commutes%20is%20perplexing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20asked%20Amazon%2C%20Apple%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20which%20have%20ambitious%20climate%20goals%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20they%20considered%20the%20potential%20environmental%20trade-offs%20in%20crafting%20their%20return-to-office%20mandates.%20All%20declined%20to%20comment%20or%20didn't%20respond%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20their%20latest%20sustainability%20reports%2C%20Amazon%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20Google%20account%20for%20employee%20commutes%20in%20their%20overall%20carbon%20footprint.%20JPMorgan%20does%20not.%20Google%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gstatic.com%2Fgumdrop%2Fsustainability%2Fgoogle-2023-environmental-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20commuting%20and%20teleworking%20contributes%3C%2Fa%3E%202%25%20of%20the%20total%20emissions%20created%20by%20the%20company.%20Amazon%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D7648d69efeb3a0b75f2d9a47cc6073534dd497afbfcd48f8d275d6e4bd385f6f%26postID%3D64d2530e29ea7163e0de2990%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fsustainability.aboutamazon.com%252Fcarbon-methodology.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20it%20counts%20emissions%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20company-provided%20shuttles%20and%20certain%20employer-subsidized%20transit%20but%20doesn't%20break%20out%20a%20specific%20total.%20Apple%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dde5fff59f18e5d767aaeb71155e925f76f0af4afa82283a29fec5087968a5e89%26postID%3D64d2530e29ea7163e0de2990%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.apple.com%252Fenvironment%252Fpdf%252FApple_Environmental_Progress_Report_2022.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20employee%20commute%20and%20business%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20accounts%20for%200.5%25%20of%20its%20emissions%2C%20which%20it%20offsets%20by%20purchasing%20carbon%20credits%20from%20projects%20that%20protect%20and%20restore%20nature.%20While%20these%20numbers%20may%20seem%20small%2C%20they%20do%20add%20up%2C%20and%20optimizing%20how%20employees%20commute%20could%20be%20an%20easy%20win%20for%20companies%20that%20ostensibly%20care%20about%20the%20future%20of%20the%20planet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EIt's%20important%20to%20recognize%20that%20working%20from%20home%20isn't%20a%20perfect%20environmental%20solution.%20We%20have%20to%20think%20about%20it%20holistically.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ESchneider%20Electric%2C%20which%20makes%20hardware%20and%20software%20to%20manage%20energy%20in%20buildings%2C%20is%20focused%20on%20making%20its%20own%20offices%20as%20sustainable%20as%20possible%20and%20offering%20employees%20flexibility%20to%20work%20from%20home.%20Tony%20Johnson%2C%20the%20director%20of%20hub%20sites%20and%20workplace%20strategy%2C%20said%20these%20efforts%20began%20around%202015.%20Since%20then%2C%20Schneider%20Electric%20has%20shrunk%20its%20offices%20from%20300%20to%20about%20200%20in%20North%20America.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20recognized%20that%20not%20everybody%20wants%20or%20needs%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20every%20day%20of%20the%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20build%20relationships%20that%20drive%20innovation%20virtually.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchneider%20asks%20its%2035%2C000%20employees%20in%20North%20America%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20at%20least%20two%20days%20a%20week%20and%20is%20pursuing%20electric%20vehicles%20for%20those%20who%20regularly%20drive%20to%20meet%20with%20customers.%20The%20company's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.se.com%2Fww%2Fen%2Fassets%2F564%2Fdocument%2F396659%2F2022-sustainability-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20sustainability%20report%20shows%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20emissions%20from%20its%20own%20offices%20and%20manufacturing%20sites%20around%20the%20world%20are%20decreasing%2C%20while%20emissions%20from%20employee%20commuting%20increased.%20Both%20categories%20account%20for%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20Schneider%20Electric's%20overall%20carbon%20footprint.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20complicated%20problem%2C%20and%20we're%20learning%20as%20we%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said.%20%26quot%3BSeveral%20years%20ago%2C%20no%20one%20was%20talking%20about%20how%20their%20vendors%20were%20impacting%20the%20planet.%20Now%2C%20we're%20trying%20to%20make%20sure%20our%20furniture%20supplier%20recycles%20or%20refurbishes.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Rachel%2C%20finding%20another%20job%20that%20is%20fully%20remote%20would%20be%20ideal.%20She%20already%20negotiated%20with%20her%20current%20employer%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20two%20days%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20as%20opposed%20to%20five%20%E2%80%94%20and%20doesn't%20think%20they%20will%20budge%20any%20further.%20That's%20left%20Rachel%20thinking%20about%20the%20ripple%20effects%20of%20commuting%20to%20work%20%E2%80%94%20the%20environmental%20impact%2C%20the%20weight%20on%20her%20mental%20health%2C%20even%20the%20wear%20and%20tear%20on%20her%20cars%20and%20the%20roads.%20For%20all%20these%20reasons%2C%20she's%20determined%20that%20going%20into%20the%20office%20simply%20isn't%20worth%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20go%20in%20because%20our%20CEO%20likes%20to%20have%20people%20to%20talk%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20our%20presence%20is%20generating%20amazing%20ideas%20or%20networking.%20My%20boss%20just%20likes%20a%20more%20traditional%20work%20environment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fcatherine-boudreau%5C%22%3ECatherine%20Boudreau%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20senior%20sustainability%20reporter%20at%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-remote-work-from-home-commute-companies-climate-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692264481000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da92d85e5d5a00195ddcfb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-remote-work-from-home-commute-companies-climate-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20that%20brag%20about%20being%20their%20climate%20goals%20are%20trying%20to%20end%20remote%20work%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20move%20could%20exacerbate%20global%20warming.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-remote-work-from-home-commute-companies-climate-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Britney%20Spears%2C%20Husband%20Sam%20Asghari%20File%20For%20Divorce%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESinger%20Britney%20Spears%20and%20her%20husband%20Sam%20Asghari%20have%20filed%20for%20divorce%20after%2014%20months%20of%20marriage%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66529567%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20news%20was%20first%20reported%20by%20%3Cem%3ETMZ%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20a%20source%20later%20told%20the%20Associated%20Press%20news%20agency%20that%20Mr%20Asghari%20had%20filed%20for%20divorce.%20The%20filing%20happened%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20outlet%20further%20said.%20Ms%20Spears%20and%20Mr%20Asghari%20got%20married%20in%20June%209%2C%202022%2C%20in%20Thousand%20Oaks%2C%20California.%20The%20guests%20included%20Selena%20Gomez%2C%20Drew%20Barrymore%2C%20Paris%20Hilton%20and%20Madonna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tmz.com%2F2023%2F08%2F16%2Fsam-asghari-files-divorce-britney-spears-prenup%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETMZ%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mr%20Asghari%20cited%20%26quot%3Birreconcilable%20differences%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20also%20asking%20for%20the%20star%20to%20pay%20spousal%20support%20along%20with%20his%20attorney's%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSam%20has%20yet%20to%20determine%20the%20full%20nature%20and%20extent%20of%20the%20separate%20property%20assets%20and%20obligations%20of%20each%20party%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20outlet%20cited%20from%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20various%20items%20of%20community%20and%20quasi-community%20assets%20and%20debts%2C%20the%20full%20nature%20and%20extent%20of%20which%20are%20unknown%20to%20Sam%20at%20this%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20he%20listed%20their%20separation%20date%20as%20July%2028%2C%20as%20per%C2%A0%3Cem%3ETMZ%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Spears'%20marriage%20took%20place%20five%20months%20after%20a%20Los%20Angeles%20judge%20dissolved%20a%2013-year%20conservatorship%20overseen%20by%20Spears'%20father%20-%20an%20arrangement%20the%20singer%20said%20had%20prevented%20her%20from%20having%20a%20contraceptive%20IUD%20removed%20despite%20her%20desire%20for%20more%20children.%20She%20is%20already%20mother%20to%20two%20teen%20sons%2C%20Sean%20and%20Jayden%2C%20with%20h