witter.com%2Fisro%2Fstatus%2F1692083786895474724%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2017%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20to%20the%20propulsion%20module%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20propulsion%20module%20is%20the%20primary%20workhorse%20of%20the%20spacecraft%2C%20responsible%20for%20carrying%20the%20lander%20module%20to%20a%20safe%20orbit%20around%20the%20Moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ISRO%2C%20the%20propulsion%20module%20will%20continue%20to%20orbit%20Earth%20for%20months%20or%20even%20years%2C%20conducting%20spectroscopic%20studies%20of%20its%20atmosphere%20and%20measuring%20the%20polarisation%20of%20light%20from%20Earth's%20clouds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLM%20is%20successfully%20separated%20from%20the%20Propulsion%20Module%20(PM).%20LM%20is%20set%20to%20descend%20to%20a%20slightly%20lower%20orbit%20upon%20a%20deboosting%20planned%20for%20tomorrow%2C%26quot%3B%20ISRO%20wrote%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EChandrayaan-3%20Mission%3A%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Propulsion%20Module%20continues%20its%20journey%20in%20the%20current%20orbit%20for%20months%2Fyears.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20SHAPE%20payload%20onboard%20it%20would%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%98%91%EF%B8%8F%20perform%20spectroscopic%20study%20of%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20and%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%98%91%EF%B8%8F%20measure%20the%20variations%20in%20polarization%20from%20the%20clouds%20on%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20ISRO%20(%40isro)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fisro%2Fstatus%2F1692084156585627923%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2017%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%20was%20launched%20into%20space%20by%20the%20LVM3%20rocket%20from%20the%20Satish%20Dhawan%20Space%20Centre%20in%20Sriharikota%20on%20July%2014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20propulsion%20module%20carried%20the%20lander%20Vikram%20and%20the%20rover%20Pragyaan%20configuration%20to%20a%20100-kilometre%20lunar%20orbit.%20The%20lander%20then%20separated%20from%20the%20propulsion%20module%20and%20will%20now%20attempt%20a%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20propulsion%20module%20carries%20the%20SHAPE%20payload%2C%20which%20will%20analyse%20the%20spectral%20and%20polarimetric%20properties%20of%20light%20from%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20SHAPE%20payload%20onboard%20would%20perform%20spectroscopic%20study%20of%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20and%20measure%20the%20variations%20in%20polarisation%20from%20the%20clouds%20on%20Earth%20to%20accumulate%20signatures%20of%20exoplanets%20that%20would%20qualify%20for%20our%20habitability!%26quot%3B%20ISRO%20wrote%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%2C%20a%20follow-up%20mission%20to%20Chandrayaan-2%2C%20will%20attempt%20to%20land%20a%20spacecraft%20on%20the%20moon%20and%20deploy%20the%20rover%20to%20explore%20the%20lunar%20surface.%20The%20rover%20will%20collect%20data%20on%20the%20composition%20and%20geology%20of%20the%20moon%2C%20which%20will%20help%20scientists%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20history%20and%20evolution%20of%20our%20nearest%20celestial%20neighbor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20its%20primary%20objective%20of%20landing%20a%20spacecraft%20on%20the%20Moon%2C%20Chandrayaan-3%20will%20also%20conduct%20in-situ%20scientific%20experiments%20to%20study%20the%20lunar%20environment%2C%20such%20as%20its%20history%2C%20geology%2C%20and%20potential%20for%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%20is%20carrying%20six%20scientific%20payloads%20to%20study%20the%20lunar%20soil%2C%20capture%20photographs%20of%20Earth%20from%20lunar%20orbit%2C%20and%20perform%20other%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20its%2014-day%20mission%20(one%20lunar%20day)%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%2C%20Chandrayaan-3%20will%20conduct%20a%20series%20of%20groundbreaking%20experiments%20using%20its%20payloads%20RAMBHA%20and%20ILSA.%20These%20experiments%20will%20study%20the%20lunar%20atmosphere%20and%20subsurface%20to%20better%20understand%20its%20mineral%20composition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rover%20Pragyaan%20will%20use%20its%20laser%20beams%20to%20melt%20a%20piece%20of%20the%20lunar%20surface%2C%20called%20regolith%2C%20and%20analsze%20the%20gases%20emitted%20in%20the%20process.%20Through%20this%20mission%2C%20India%20will%20not%20only%20access%20a%20wealth%20of%20knowledge%20about%20the%20lunar%20surface%20but%20also%20its%20potential%20for%20human%20habitation%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spacecraft%20is%20expected%20to%20land%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20at%205%3A47%20pm%20on%20August%2023.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692262620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Frotit2lc_chandrayaan-3-launch_625x300_14_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-vikram-lander-pragyaan-rover-chandrayaan-3-what-happens-to-the-propulsion-module-after-separation-4305124%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chandrayaan-3%20spacecraft's%20lander%20Vikram%20today%20successfully%20separated%20from%20its%20propulsion%20module%20and%20continued%20its%20journey%20towards%20the%20Moon%20where%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20make%20a%20soft%20landing%20on%20August%2023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-vikram-lander-pragyaan-rover-chandrayaan-3-what-happens-to-the-propulsion-module-after-separation-4305124%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-vikram-lander-pragyaan-rover-chandrayaan-3-what-happens-to-the-propulsion-module-after-separation-4305124%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan