%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20world.%20It%20was%20said%20that%20India%20would%20hog%20all%20the%20jobs%20from%20the%20West.%20India%E2%80%99s%20call-centres%2C%20the%20emergence%20of%20companies%20like%20Infosys%20and%20success%20of%20TCS%2C%20and%20legends%20that%20timetables%20for%20the%20London%20tube%20were%20drawn%20up%20in%20Bangalore%20were%20the%20stuff%20of%20TV%20soaps.%20Typical%20characters%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Big%20Bang%20Theory%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ESilicon%20Valley%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20distinct%20%E2%80%98Indian%E2%80%99%20accents%2C%20they%20were%20geeks%20who%20knew%20their%200s%20from%20their%201s.%20At%20Cupertino%20in%20the%20canteen%2C%20Telugu%20is%20said%20to%20be%20the%20second-most%20popular%20language%20after%20English.%20Indian-origin%20persons%20heading%20several%20Big%20Tech%20ventures%20added%20to%20this%20%E2%80%98India%20is%20about%20digital%E2%80%99%20mythology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20then%20is%20it%20not%20natural%20for%20a%20%E2%80%98Vishwaguru%E2%80%99%20nation%20to%20try%20and%20use%20this%2C%20like%20Yoga%20and%20Ayurveda%2C%20for%20purposes%20of%20publicity%2C%20market%20itself%20as%20a%20model%20for%20democracies%20for%20the%20best%20handling%20of%20data%20and%20the%20net%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%20that%20the%20first%20attempts%20to%20mine%20the%20G20%20into%20an%20internal%20PR%20coup%20and%20spin%20a%20routine%20rotational%20presidency%20into%20a%20personalised%2C%20crowning%20glory%20moment%20for%20the%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20were%20put%20into%20motion.%20A%20different%20push%2C%20outward%2C%20of%20owning%20a%20term%20called%20%E2%80%98techade%E2%80%99%2C%20trying%20to%20get%20India%20to%20grab%20centrestage%20and%20be%20a%20model%20for%20how%20data%20and%20the%20digital%20world%20was%20organised%2C%20was%20also%20set%20in%20motion%20last%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENiti%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famitabhkant.co.in%2Fupload%2Farticles%2F84797658363a92beac3ea54.19991689_India-will-set-new-data-standards-in-G20-stint.pdf%5C%22%3EAmitabh%20Kant%20spoke%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20style%20now%20perfected%20by%20the%20government%2C%20of%20double-speak%20mashing%20buzz%20words%20in%20vogue%20globally%2C%20but%20standing%20for%20the%20opposite%20(like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Flies-insistence-and-disregard-for-evidence-the-journey-of-love-jihad-laws%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Freedom%20of%20Religion%20Bills%E2%80%99%20are%20designed%20to%20do%20the%20exact%20opposite%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Kant%20spoke%20of%20the%20data%20%E2%80%9Cgold%20standard%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20he%20said%20%E2%80%9Cemphasises%20on%20nations%20to%20invest%20in%20self-evaluation%20of%20their%20data%20governance%20architecture%2C%20calls%20for%20modernisation%20of%20national%20data%20systems%20to%20incorporate%20citizen%20voice%20and%20preferences%20regularly%2C%20advances%20principles%20of%20transparency%20for%20data%20governance%20and%20finally%20brings%20to%20the%20forefront%20the%20need%20for%20strategic%20leadership%20on%20data%20for%20sustainable%20development%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESerious%20limitations%20on%20handling%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20date%20with%20data%20and%20the%20digital%20ecosystem%20it%20is%20creating%20have%20serious%20limitations%20and%2C%20far%20from%20trying%20to%20be%20what%20the%20G20%20should%20aspire%20to%20do%2C%20may%20well%20be%20an%20index%20of%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20was%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20%E2%80%93%20supposedly%20to%20protect%20citizen%20data%20%E2%80%93%20last%20year%2C%20when%20a%20parliamentary%20committee%20examined%20it%20and%20suggested%20several%20changes.%20But%20it%20was%20withdrawn%20abruptly%20without%20giving%20any%20reasons.%20A%20reinvented%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20this%20year%20and%20rushed%20through%20parliament.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-08-07%2Findia-s-lower-house-of-parliament-approves-data-privacy-bill%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20described%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20boon%20for%20global%20enterprises%20such%20as%20Google%20and%C2%A0Meta%2C%20as%20it%20eases%20data%20flows%20and%20reduces%20their%20compliance%20burdens%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Bill%20offers%20little%20protection%20for%20citizens%2C%20and%20exempts%20the%20biggest%20data%20fiduciary%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20government%20(and%20any%20other%20company%20it%20may%20decide%20to%20exempt%2C%20without%20having%20to%20cite%20reasons)%20from%20accountability.%20The%20Union%20minister%20misleadingly%20compared%20the%20Bill%20to%20EU%E2%80%99s%20landmark%20General%20Data%C2%A0Protection%C2%A0Regulation%C2%A0(GDPR).%20Claiming%20that%20the%20GDPR%20gives%20%E2%80%9C16%20exemptions%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20DPDP%20Bill%20gives%20only%20%E2%80%9Cfour%20exemptions%E2%80%9D.%20But%20as%20was%20pointed%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechpolicy.press%2Fassessing-indias-digital-personal-data-protection-bill%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20Tech%20Policy%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20technology%20journalist%20Aditi%20Agrawal%2C%20%E2%80%9Cin%20India%E2%80%99s%20version%20of%20the%20Bill%20they%E2%80%99ve%20used%20commas.%20So%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20you%20have%20six%20listed%20exemptions.%20But%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20each%20of%20the%20sub-clauses%2C%20there%20are%20actually%20many%20more.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Digital%20India%20Has%20Run%20Out%20of%20Freedoms%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fdigital-india-has-run-out-of-freedoms%5C%22%3EDigital%20India%20Has%20Run%20Out%20of%20Freedoms%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrivacy%20is%20the%20lens%20through%20which%20the%20task%20of%20protecting%20citizens%E2%80%99%20data%20from%20misuse%20is%20framed%20in%20the%20GDPR.%20But%20in%20India%2C%20the%20shift%20from%20the%20first%20draft%20Bill%20that%20the%20Justice%20B.N.%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20put%20out%20in%202018%2C%20a%20year%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20on%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20being%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%20is%20drastic.%20The%20draft%20has%20seen%20at%20least%20five%20versions.%20The%20thrust%20is%20now%20on%20allowing%20government%20and%20companies%20the%20ease%20of%20mining%20citizens%E2%80%99%20data.%20There%20is%20no%20independent%20data%20protection%20authority%20provided%20for.%20India%E2%80%99s%20deployment%20of%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20without%20proper%20consultation%20and%20the%20rampant%20use%20of%20cameras%20in%20public%20places%20makes%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F1290708%2Ftop-surveilled-countries-worldwide%2F%5C%22%3Eamong%20the%20most%20surveilled%20and%20data-hungry%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20cybersecurity%20record%20has%20been%20a%20cause%20of%20grave%20concern.%20Health%20data%2C%20regarded%20as%20the%20most%20sensitive%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fcowin-data-leak-certin-update-scam-identity-theft-aadhaar%5C%22%3Ewas%20leaked%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20COWIN%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20centralised%20portal%20for%20COVID-19%20vaccines.%20A%20bot%20via%20Telegram%20is%20said%20to%20have%20been%20able%20to%20made%20public%20personal%20details%20like%20names%2C%20Aadhaar%20numbers%20and%20passport%20details%20upon%20entering%20phone%20numbers.%C2%A0Such%20break-ins%20were%20said%20to%20have%20happened%20at%20least%20thrice%2C%20though%20the%20last%20time%20in%20June%20got%20an%20acknowledgement%20this%20summer.%20The%20most%20worrying%20thing%20is%20that%20there%20is%20no%20process%20to%20address%20breaches%20or%20reveal%20who%20has%20been%20held%20accountable.%20There%20is%20no%20record%20of%20any%20investigation%20being%20carried%20out%20by%20CERT-In.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20premier%20medical%20institute%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20in%20Delhi%2C%20was%20down%20for%2019%20days%20as%20the%20system%20was%20hacked%20by%20cybercriminals%20and%20as%20the%20minister%20later%20admitted%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Faiims-servers-cyberattack-ransomware-rajya-sabha%5C%22%3Eone%20TB%20of%20encrypted%20data%20from%20the%20hospital%20taken.%3C%2Fa%3E%20No%20process%2C%20follow%20up%20or%20confidence%20inducing%20measures.%20Again%2C%20no%20process%20established%20for%20the%20hacks%20or%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20pieces%20that%20make%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98digital%E2%80%99%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20start%2C%20internet%20penetration%20in%20India%20is%20way%20behind%20the%20world%20penetration%20of%2063%25.%20It%20was%2046%25%20in%202021%2C%20which%20places%20it%20at%20rank%20120%20in%20the%20world%2C%20as%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fopinion%2Fonline-views%2Fits-time-to-double-down-on-our-digital-expansion-11691512081891.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rules%20for%20social%20media%20and%20technology%20platforms%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meity.gov.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Ffiles%2FInformation%2520Technology%2520%2528Intermediary%2520Guidelines%2520and%2520Digital%2520Media%2520Ethics%2520Code%2529%2520Rules%252C%25202021%2520%2528updated%252006.04.2023%2529-.pdf%5C%22%3EInformation%20Technology%20(Intermediary%20Guidelines%20and%20Digital%20Media%20Ethics%20Code)%20Rules%2C%202021%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20were%20firmed%20up%20in%20April%20this%20year%2C%20encompass%20websites%20of%20all%20kinds.%20They%20controversially%20and%20deliberately%20confuse%20government%20control%20with%20regulation.%20A%20%E2%80%98fact-checking%20unit%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20the%20powers%20to%20decree%20anything%20online%20as%20not%20true%20and%20it%20can%20be%20taken%20down.%20A%20stand-up%20comedian%2C%20Kunal%20Kamra%2C%20as%20well%20as%20media%20bodies%20have%20challenged%20the%20rules%20and%20spoken%20of%20their%20power%20to%20silence%20voices.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20following%20the%20diktat%20%E2%80%98Rome%20has%20spoken%E2%80%99%20which%20implies%20that%20whatever%20the%20government%20speaks%20is%20final%20and%20no%20one%20has%20the%20right%20to%20express%20their%20views%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kamra%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20argued%20in%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBig%20Tech%3A%20Intimidated%20or%20happy%20to%20help%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBig%20Tech%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%20must%20face%20serious%20scrutiny.%20WhatsApp%20has%20teamed%20up%20with%20a%20billionaire%2C%20the%20Ambanis%2C%20putting%20paid%20to%20any%20ideas%20Silicon%20Valley%20may%20have%20nursed%20about%20being%20seen%20as%20disruptive%20or%20with%20the%20average%20Joe.%20Meta%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20produce%20an%20honest%20report%20about%20fake%20news%20and%20hate%20speech%20in%20India%20and%20its%20impact%20have%20been%20written%20about%20in%20detail.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20also%20run%20investigations%20about%20Big%20Tech%20feeling%20pressured%20to%20not%20take%20down%20posts%20they%20deem%20as%20harmful%2C%20false%20or%20spreading%20hate.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20where%20the%20Hindu-nationalist%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20%E2%80%94%20part%20of%20the%20coalition%20behind%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20political%20rise%20%E2%80%94%20deploys%20inflammatory%20rhetoric%20against%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20minority%2C%20misinformation%20and%20hate%20speech%20can%20translate%20into%20real-life%20violence%2C%20making%20the%20stakes%20of%20these%20limited%20safety%20protocols%20particularly%20high%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2021%2F10%2F24%2Findia-facebook-misinformation-hate-speech%2F%5C%22%3Eit%20wrote%20in%202021.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwitter%E2%80%99s%20founder%2C%20Jack%20Dorsey%20said%20in%20June%20that%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20made%20%E2%80%9Cmany%20requests%E2%80%9D%20to%20Twitter%20during%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests%20for%20the%20deletion%20of%20content%20by%20journalists%20critical%20of%20official%20policy%20and%20also%20threatened%20to%20shut%20down%20Twitter%20in%20India%20and%20raid%20its%20employees%E2%80%99%20homes.%20The%20IT%20minister%20dismissed%20his%20claims%20as%20baseless%2C%20but%20the%20very%20public%20sparring%20between%20government%20and%20Twitter%20in%202021%20saw%20the%20police%20being%20deployed%20in%20two%20cities%2C%20and%20this%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20public%20record%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fjack-dorsey-rajeev-chandrasekhar-twitter-takedown-india-farmers-protests%5C%22%3Eas%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EPodcast%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fpodcast-india-has-been-the-leading-country-in-internet-shutdowns-for-5-years-thats-alarming%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Podcast%3A%20India%20Has%20Been%20the%20Leading%20Country%20in%20Internet%20Shutdowns%20for%205%20Years.%20That%E2%80%99s%20Alarming.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIndia%20Has%20Been%20the%20Leading%20Country%20in%20Internet%20Shutdowns%20for%205%20Years.%20That%E2%80%99s%20Alarming.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cyber-world%20being%20soaked%20with%20misinformation%20is%20something%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Finternational%2Farchive%2F2019%2F04%2Findia-misinformation-election-fake-news%2F586123%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Atlantic%20pointed%20to%20in%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%E2%80%9CMany%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20misinformation%20campaigns%20are%20developed%20and%20run%20by%20political%20parties%20with%20nationwide%20cyberarmies%3B%20they%20target%20not%20only%20political%20opponents%2C%20but%20also%20religious%20minorities%20and%C2%A0dissenting%20individuals%2C%20with%20propaganda%20rooted%20in%20domestic%20divisions%20and%20prejudices.%E2%80%9D%20A%20Study%20by%20the%20Oxford%20Internet%20Institute%20of%20Oxford%20University%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9Cover%20a%20third%20of%20visual%20content%20(predominantly%20images)%20shared%20in%20BJP%20WhatsApp%20groups%20(34.5%25)%20was%20%E2%80%9Cdivisive%20and%20conspirational%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20the%20figure%20at%2028.5%25%20for%20the%20Congress%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20internet%20and%20democracy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20societies%20and%20governments%20treat%20the%20internet%20is%20emerging%20as%20a%20shorthand%20for%20freedoms%20and%20the%20status%20of%20democracies%2C%20the%20world%20over.%20Much%20is%20written%20about%20how%20the%20digital%20world%20in%20China%20(firewalled)%2C%20Iran%20(restricted)%20or%20Russia%20(bot%20farm-filled)%20is.%20But%20there%20is%20little%20scrutiny%20of%20India%2C%20as%20it%20tries%20to%20sell%20its%20digital%20payment%20infrastructure%20or%20its%20public%20digital%20infrastructure%20as%20elements%20the%20world%20should%20emulate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20India%20is%20also%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20internet%20shutdown%20capital.%20Last%20year%2C%2045%25%20of%20all%20internet%20shutdowns%20were%20in%20India.%20For%20the%20past%20five%20consecutive%20years%2C%20India%20has%20topped%20the%20global%20list%20of%20states%20that%20cut%20off%20the%20internet%20for%20their%20citizens.%20Manipur%20this%20time%20saw%20100%20days%20straight%20minus%20the%20internet%2C%20curbing%20information%20and%20also%20the%20rights%20of%20those%20seeking%20redress%20or%20help.%20Education%20and%20utilities%20suffer%20greatly%20too.%20In%20India%2C%20the%2