ion%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSeven%20of%20the%2021%20defendants%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20charges%20against%20them%2C%20which%20included%20tax%20evasion%2C%20sale%20of%20substandard%20or%20counterfeit%20medicines%2C%20abuse%20of%20office%2C%20negligence%2C%20forgery%2C%20and%20bribery%2C%E2%80%9D%20Reuters%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwho-uzbekistan-cough-syrup-noida-product-alert%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Doc-1%20Max%20and%20one%20other%20cough%20syrup%20manufactured%20by%20Marion%20Biotech%20contained%20diethylene%20glycol%20(DEG)%20and%20ethylene%20glycol%20(EG)%20in%20unacceptable%20levels.%20Three%20people%20linked%20with%20the%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fuzbekistan-child-deaths-three-of-noida-based-firm-arrested-for-contaminated-medicines%5C%22%3Ehad%20been%20arrested%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Indian%20authorities%20in%20March%20this%20year%20after%20the%20controversy%20erupted.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692252041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F18153208%2Fpexels-cottonbro-studio-5858861.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fuzbekistan-alleges-indian-company-paid-33000-bribe-to-put-cough-syrup-in-market%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20number%20of%20deaths%20linked%20to%20the%20cough%20syrup%20cited%20by%20the%20prosecutors%20in%20court%20%E2%80%93%2065%20%E2%80%93%20is%20far%20higher%20than%20what%20was%20previously%20reported%20from%20Uzbekistan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fuzbekistan-alleges-indian-company-paid-33000-bribe-to-put-cough-syrup-in-market%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2220%2C000%20urged%20to%20evacuate%20by%20road%20an